The Operation Tool lets you manipulate your divided panels or materials you’ve used.
The Divide Tool allows you to slice across the canvas to create comic panels. Make sure you start your swipe from one border to the other to make you panel.
The Shape (Curve) Tool allows you to make a curve with whichever brush you have selected.
The Shape (Ellipse) Tool allows you to make a circle with whichever brush you have selected.
The Shape (Straight Line) Tool allows you to make a straight line with whichever brush you have selected.
The Shape (Polygon) Tool allows you to make a custom shape with whichever brush you have selected.
The Shape (Zigzag) Tool allows you to make zigzags with whichever brush you have selected.
The Shape (Rectangle) Tool allows you to make a rectangle with whichever brush you have selected.
The Erase Tool allows you to erase things that you have drawn on the canvas. You can change the size and opacity in the Brush Settings Menu.

The Fill Tool (ellipse) allows you to fill in color in an area in the shape of an ellipse.
The Fill Tool (polygon) allows you to create a polygon filled with your currently selected color. Click around the canvas to create a shape and fill it with color.
The Fill Tool (rectangle) allows you to fill in color in an area in the shape of a rectangle.
The Gradient Tool（Ellipse）allows you to make a circular shaped gradation 。There are two types of gradients. Foreground-Background and Foreground.
The Gradient Tool(linear）allows you to make a linear color gradation. There are two types of gradients. Foreground-Background and Foreground.

The Brush Tool allows you to draw on the canvas. When you want to change your brush size, opacity, color, or type you can do so in the Brush Settings Menu
"Touch the area you'd like to make your center point."

The Select Tool (Ellipse) allows you to make a selection in the shape of a oval. While the + button is highlighted additional selections can be added. When the - button is selected selected areas can be deselected.
The Select Erase Tool allows you to erase parts of selections to unselect areas you don’t want selected.
The Select Pen Tool allows you to draw on areas in order to make selections.

The Select Tool (polygon) allows you to create a selection by clicking around the canvas. You can add to a selection by using the tool and holding the plus key while clicking. You can remove parts of the selection by holding down the - key.

The Select Tool (Rectangle) allows you to make a selection in the shape of a rectangle. While the + button is highlighted additional selections can be added. When the - button is selected selected areas can be deselected.
The Lasso Tool allows you to make freehand selections. While the + button is highlighted additional selections can be added. When the - button is selected selected areas can be deselected.
The Snap Tool allows you to set up guides or vanishing points. You can use the guides to draw lines coming from a vanishing point or make parallel lines or draw curves.
The Eyedropper Tool allows you to select a color from where ever you click on the canvas.
The Text Tool allows you to type text on the canvas or edit text that you’ve already put on the canvas.You can use the tool to enter text vertically or horizontally.

Objects inside the selection can be scaled, rotated or moved. Dragging the white squares will allow you to scale the object. Dragging inside of the selection will move the object. Dragging outside of the selection will rotate the object.
The Magic Wand Tool allows you to select colors or enclosed areas with just one click.
